I think those who are
more targeted and bolder

00:49:03.490 --> 00:49:04.910
in their approach
to buybacks, are

00:49:04.910 --> 00:49:07.159
going to continue to be able
to create value that way.

00:49:07.159 --> 00:49:10.450
So I think a lot of it has to
do with your approach to that.

00:49:10.450 --> 00:49:12.160
So that's in the
case of buybacks.

00:49:12.160 --> 00:49:13.450
3G is just fascinating.

00:49:13.450 --> 00:49:15.158
It's just fascinating
to see what they're

00:49:15.158 --> 00:49:16.780
doing across these industries.

00:49:16.780 --> 00:49:21.095
And I don't know-- I'm
curious to see what that's

00:49:21.095 --> 00:49:22.720
going to look like
five years from now,

00:49:22.720 --> 00:49:27.200
but have proven, across a
range of businesses now,

00:49:27.200 --> 00:49:31.640
the ability to grow cash flow,
increase margins through zero

00:49:31.640 --> 00:49:38.340
based budgeting, reducing
costs without material

00:49:38.340 --> 00:49:41.110
declines in revenues.

00:49:41.110 --> 00:49:43.050
In many cases, they
haven't shown the ability

00:49:43.050 --> 00:49:44.841
to grow revenues, but
they were in business

00:49:44.841 --> 00:49:46.470
that were pretty mature anyway.

00:49:46.470 --> 00:49:51.410
So I think it's early days
still in seeing how that's

00:49:51.410 --> 00:49:54.340
going to play out over
time, but the early data

00:49:54.340 --> 00:49:56.012
is very interesting.

00:49:56.012 --> 00:49:57.720
And I think it's an
interesting question.

00:49:57.720 --> 00:50:00.180
I think it's an
ethical question.

00:50:00.180 --> 00:50:03.260
Because a company may
have been very prosperous

00:50:03.260 --> 00:50:05.550
over a long period of time,
like CBS in the example

00:50:05.550 --> 00:50:09.910
I talked about before, and it's
created a corporate structure

00:50:09.910 --> 00:50:13.660
that just grew organically
over time, like Kudzu,

00:50:13.660 --> 00:50:16.890
but isn't necessarily
rational relative

00:50:16.890 --> 00:50:19.450
to the business itself,
and sort of grew

00:50:19.450 --> 00:50:23.180
because of
institutional momentums,

00:50:23.180 --> 00:50:30.570
is it ethical to streamline
those businesses so that they

00:50:30.570 --> 00:50:33.090
run more efficiently, if it
doesn't change the customer

00:50:33.090 --> 00:50:34.530
experience?

00:50:34.530 --> 00:50:35.090
I don't know.

00:50:35.090 --> 00:50:37.720
I think that's a really
interesting, ethical question.

00:50:37.720 --> 00:50:40.240
I think you could certainly
make an argument that you're not

00:50:40.240 --> 00:50:45.760
necessarily doing a favor for
those in bloated hierarchies

00:50:45.760 --> 00:50:48.056
to protect their
jobs at ad infinitum.

00:50:48.056 --> 00:50:49.680
I'm not sure that's
better for society.

00:50:49.680 --> 00:50:54.300
I'm not sure that
what 3G is doing isn't

00:50:54.300 --> 00:50:56.740
the right long term-- even
though it causes dislocation,

00:50:56.740 --> 00:50:58.970
it's very unfortunate for
those who lose their jobs,

00:50:58.970 --> 00:51:01.430
it's unclear to
me that that's not

00:51:01.430 --> 00:51:02.800
good for society, longer term.

00:51:02.800 --> 00:51:03.341
I don't know.

00:51:03.341 --> 00:51:05.154
I think it's an
interesting question.

